## Summary

Adds a minimal VitePress documentation site under `docs/` (homepage + getting-started) and a GitHub Actions workflow that builds and deploys it to GitHub Pages on every push to `main`.

### What's in this PR

- `docs/.vitepress/config.mts` ‚Äî VitePress configuration (Quillr branding, nav, sidebar, footer, local search, social link to GitHub). Excludes the pre-existing `docs/journeys|research|stories|traceability/` directories via `srcExclude` so VitePress does not attempt to render them ‚Äî they use a project-specific `layout: doc` frontmatter that is not a valid VitePress layout.
- `docs/index.md` ‚Äî homepage using VitePress' `layout: home` with hero + features, summarizing both packages (`@kooshapari/quillts` and `httpora-core`).
- `docs/getting-started.md` ‚Äî installation and quick-start snippets for both TypeScript and Rust, plus development commands.
- `docs/package.json` + `docs/package-lock.json` ‚Äî minimal VitePress 1.6.3 site, pinned and reproducible (`npm ci`).
- `docs/.gitignore` ‚Äî ignores `node_modules`, `.vitepress/cache`, `.vitepress/dist`.
- `.github/workflows/docs.yml` ‚Äî Pages workflow using `actions/configure-pages@v5`, `actions/upload-pages-artifact@v3`, `actions/deploy-pages@v4` as specified. Triggers on push to `main` and on `workflow_dispatch`. Concurrency group cancels in-progress deploys. Permissions scoped to the minimum (`contents: read`, `pages: write`, `id-token: write`).

### Strict scope

Touched **only** `docs/`, `.github/workflows/docs.yml`, and `docs/package.json` (plus its lockfile companion required for reproducible CI). No files under `src/`, no `.rs` files, and no `Cargo.toml`/`Cargo.lock` were modified.

### Local quality checks run

All checks below were run locally on `feat/ghpages-docs` after the changes:

| Check | Result |
|---|---|
| `npm run lint` (eslint `src`) | PASS ‚Äî 0 errors |
| `npm run format:check` (prettier on `src/**/*.{ts,json,md}`) | PASS ‚Äî all matched files use Prettier style |
| `npm run check` (`tsc --noEmit`) | PASS ‚Äî clean |
| `npm test` (vitest) | PASS ‚Äî 23/23 tests across 3 files |
| `npm run build` (`tsc`) | PASS ‚Äî clean |
| `cd docs && npm run build` (VitePress) | PASS ‚Äî built in ~5‚Äì15s; `index.html`, `getting-started.html`, and `404.html` produced under `docs/.vitepress/dist/` |
| `cargo test --manifest-path crates/httpora-core/Cargo.toml --all-features` | PASS ‚Äî 30 unit + integration tests + 5 doctests |
| `cargo build --manifest-path crates/httpora-core/Cargo.toml --release` | PASS ‚Äî clean optimized build |
| `cargo fmt --manifest-path crates/httpora-core/Cargo.toml -- --check` | **PRE-EXISTING FAIL** ‚Äî formatting diffs in `crates/httpora-core/tests/middleware_test.rs` and `crates/httpora-core/tests/retry_test.rs`. Out of strict scope; not modified. |
| `cargo clippy --manifest-path crates/httpora-core/Cargo.toml --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` | **PRE-EXISTING FAIL** ‚Äî `clippy::manual_map` at `crates/httpora-core/src/builder.rs:100`. Out of strict scope; not modified. |

The two pre-existing rust failures are in `.rs` files explicitly excluded from the strict scope. They are unchanged on this branch and were present on `main` before this PR.

### Repo admin note

After this PR is merged, GitHub Pages must be enabled in the repo settings with **Settings ‚Üí Pages ‚Üí Source: GitHub Actions** so the workflow can deploy. The workflow file itself is otherwise self-contained.

### Verification artifact

- VitePress build output was inspected locally: `docs/.vitepress/dist/index.html` (title "Quillr", correct `<title>` and `__VP_HASH_MAP__`) and `docs/.vitepress/dist/getting-started.html` (renders the TypeScript/Rust code blocks and sidebar). The site is ready to deploy.

